    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSPersonNameComponents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object encapsulates the components of a person's name in an extendable, object-oriented manner. It is used to specify a person's name by providing the components comprising a full name: given name, middle name, family name, prefix, suffix, nickname, and phonetic representation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSPersonNameComponents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects can be used by an instance of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nspersonnamecomponentsformatter"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to create string representations suitable for display in the current locale."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The Swift overlay to the Foundation framework provides the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/personnamecomponents"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " structure, which bridges to the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nspersonnamecomponents"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " class. For more information about value types, see "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Working with Cocoa Frameworks",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Swift/Conceptual/BuildingCocoaApps/WorkingWithCocoaDataTypes.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40014216-CH6"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Using Swift with Cocoa and Objective-C (Swift 4.1)",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Swift/Conceptual/BuildingCocoaApps/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40014216"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Working with Names",
          "anchor": "1968741"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "It is important to understand that names are disjoint from a person’s identity. An individual may, at any time, have zero, one, or many names. Names cannot be used as a determination of a person’s identity, because two names may correspond to the same individual, and two people may have the same name. Nor can names be used as a determination of a person’s relation to others, because an individual may have a different family name than their relatives, and two individuals may have the same family name, but not be related."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Many locales and cultures have rules about what kinds of names are allowed and how they are structured. An "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSPersonNameComponents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object does not impose any restrictions about which combinations of properties may have values or what those values may be."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NSPersonNameComponents"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " represents only the components of a name. To represent contact information, such as postal addresses or phone numbers, in addition to a personal name, use "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/contacts/cncontact"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " or "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/contacts/cnmutablecontact"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " instead."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Name Components",
          "anchor": "1968742"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSPersonNameComponents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object encodes the following components of a personal name, which are described in detail below."
            }
          ]
        },
